    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-31T15:00:00-05:00" n="1029"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1029">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/3944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-31T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 31, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. In view of the uncertain revenue situation and acting upon the recommendation
                    of the office of the Fiscal Representative, the Haitian Government reserved
                    today the right to reduce the salaries of Government employees beginning June 1
                    in the absence of a substantial improvement in fiscal revenues. The Legation
                    approved the recommendation in the hope that economies in other expenditures
                    will be encouraged and therefore a reduction in salaries will not be
                    necessary.</p>
                <p>A reduction in salaries may cause serious repercussions on the political
                    situation and Haitian-American relations since the responsibility therefor will
                    be ascribed unfairly to the United States. In these circumstances I have
                    reserved the right to reexamine the situation before any reduction is
                    ordered.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
